DynaBooks is a lightweight, self-hosted accounting system built for DynaNav Systems Inc. The MVP focuses on the four core accounting functions that DynaNav needs immediately: invoicing (accounts receivable), journal entries (general ledger), bank payments
\hich\af1\dbch\af1\loch\f1  (accounts payable), and bank receipts (cash management). The system uses proper double-entry bookkeeping and produces standard financial reports.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15216094 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cf22\insrsid11474351 \hich\af1\dbch\af1\loch\f1 
The application is designed to be built by Claude Code using a Python Flask backend with a React frontend, powered by the python-accounting library for the double-entry engine. SQLite is used for the initial deployment, with a clear migration path to Post
\hich\af1\dbch\af1\loch\f1 greSQL when needed.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15216094 
